From: dArkOS RG56 Pro port
Subject: Fix libgo2 BGRA/RGBA color format for RGA blits

The bundled libgo2 maps DRM_FORMAT_ARGB8888/XRGB8888 to RK_FORMAT_BGRA_8888,
which causes red/blue channel inversion when RGA performs blits through the
OGA video driver. Fix by using RK_FORMAT_RGBA_8888 instead.

Extracted from BSP patch 0002-RB-invert.patch (libgo2 hunk only;
the drm_go2_ctx.c presenter hunk conflicts with christianhaitian's
existing 0008 patch which already makes the same change).

diff --git a/deps/libgo2/src/display.c b/deps/libgo2/src/display.c
index b91cf0624b..936b677fc4 100644
--- a/deps/libgo2/src/display.c
+++ b/deps/libgo2/src/display.c
@@ -550,7 +550,7 @@ static uint32_t go2_rkformat_get(uint32_t drm_fourcc)

         case DRM_FORMAT_ARGB8888:
         case DRM_FORMAT_XRGB8888:
-            return RK_FORMAT_BGRA_8888;
+            return RK_FORMAT_RGBA_8888;

         case DRM_FORMAT_RGB565:
             return RK_FORMAT_RGB_565;
